# `insuredSnapshot` key deduplication

`cars.extraAttributes.insuredSnapshot` is a flat key/value object
that is **full-replaced** (not merged) every time `app/api/policies/[id]`
PATCH receives a non-null `body.insured`. Any clone keys present in
the outgoing payload (`insured__ciNumber` AND `insured__cinumber`,
or `insured__category` AND `insured_category`) get persisted as
real fields, recorded in `_audit` as "changed from null", and
surface to the user as a phantom "you edited insured data" event
they didn't trigger.

If your task touches **any** of the following, STOP and read
[`.cursor/skills/insured-snapshot-dedupe/SKILL.md`](mdc:.cursor/skills/insured-snapshot-dedupe/SKILL.md)
**before** writing code:

- Editing `app/(dashboard)/dashboard/flows/[flow]/new/page.tsx`
  — especially `fillFormFromClient`, `fillFormFromRecord`,
  `saveClientChanges`, `doSubmit`, or the body of the React Hook
  Form pre-population effect
- Editing `lib/policies/insured-snapshot-dedupe.ts` (the helper)
- Editing the PATCH handler in `app/api/policies/[id]/route.ts`
  — the `body.insured ?? existing.insuredSnapshot` line and the
  insured cross-sync into `packagesSnapshot`
- Adding any **new** caller that constructs an `insured: {...}`
  payload and PATCHes `/api/policies/:id` (e.g. bulk-edit tools,
  cron-driven syncs, admin scripts)
- Adding a new field naming convention beyond `pkg__field` /
  `pkg_field` — the dedupe normalisation rules will need updating
- Diagnosing "audit log says insured changed but the user didn't
  type anything" / "the same value appears twice in the policy
  details view" / "I see both `insured__ciNumber` AND
  `insured__cinumber` in the DB"

## The 30-second cheatsheet

| Concern | Pattern | Don't do |
|---|---|---|
| Build outgoing `insured: {...}` payload | `JSON.stringify({ insured: dedupeInsuredSnapshot(snap) })` | Send `form.getValues()` straight through |
| Pre-populate wizard from existing record/client | Only set normalised key variants if the key is **already registered** in `form.getValues()` | Unconditionally `setVal("insured__" + lower(tail), v)` |
| Detect duplicates | `norm(k) = k.toLowerCase().replace(/^(insured\|contactinfo)_{1,2}/, "").replace(/_/g, "")` | Compare with `===` or prefix-only stripping |
| Pick which duplicate to keep | `__` beats `_`; then non-lowercase beats all-lowercase | First-seen / alphabetical / arbitrary |
| Cleanup legacy rows | `npx tsx scripts/cleanup-insured-snapshot-dupes.ts --apply` | Hand-edit JSONB via SQL |
| New dedupe in any file | `import { dedupeInsuredSnapshot } from "@/lib/policies/insured-snapshot-dedupe"` | Re-implement the rules inline |

## Three layers of defence (skill §2)

1. **Helper** at `lib/policies/insured-snapshot-dedupe.ts` — single
   source of truth for the normalisation rule.
2. **Form-fill guard** in the wizard — refuse to write a normalised
   key variant unless it's a registered form field.
3. **Save-time guard** — every wizard write path calls
   `dedupeInsuredSnapshot` on the outgoing payload.

Removing any one of these can re-introduce the bug. Removing the
helper guarantees it.

If anything above is unclear, the skill has the full contract, the
file index, the symptom-to-cause matrix, the cleanup recipe, and
the verification commands (rg greps + dry-run script + UI smoke
test) to confirm correctness.
